## Frontend

### General Guidelines

- Use Thymeleaf templates (.html) for server-side rendering
- Leverage Thymeleaf fragments for reusable components (nav, links, scripts)
- Keep JavaScript minimal - Bootstrap JS only for interactive components
- Follow progressive enhancement - ensure core functionality works without JS

### Thymeleaf Best Practices

- Use `th:replace="~{fragments/nav :: nav}"` for including fragments
- Use `th:field` for automatic form field binding (generates id, name, value)
- Use `th:errors` for displaying validation errors inline
- Use `th:if`/`th:unless` for conditional rendering, `th:each` for loops
- Use `th:text` for safe output (auto-escapes HTML)
- Use `th:href="@{/path}"` for URL generation with context path
- CSRF tokens automatically included by Thymeleaf Security
- Use `sec:authorize="isAuthenticated()"` for conditional auth-based rendering

### Bootstrap 5 Styling

- Use Bootstrap grid (container, row, col-*) for responsive layouts
- Apply utility classes for spacing (mb-3, mt-4, py-3, gap-2)
- Leverage semantic colors (btn-primary, btn-success, btn-danger, alert-success)
- Use Bootstrap components (cards, tables, forms, alerts, badges)
- Apply responsive utilities (d-none, d-md-block) for mobile-first design
- Use Flexbox utilities (d-flex, justify-content-between, align-items-center)
- Minimize custom CSS - prefer Bootstrap utilities

### Forms

- Display validation errors inline with `th:errors` next to fields
- Return to form view (not redirect) when validation fails
- Always use `<label>` with `for` attribute matching input `id`
- Apply `required` attribute for mandatory fields
- Set `autofocus` on first field for keyboard navigation
- Use forms (POST) for DELETE operations to include CSRF protection

### Tables

- Use `table-striped` and `table-hover` for better UX
- Use `table-responsive` wrapper for mobile horizontal scrolling
- Display "No data" messages with `th:if="${#lists.isEmpty()}"`
- Use `btn-sm` for table action buttons with semantic colors
- Use badge components for status indicators

### Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML5 elements (header, nav, main, section)
- Apply heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3) correctly
- Use `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation
- Use `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Use Bootstrap's semantic color system for sufficient contrast

### User Feedback

- Use Bootstrap alerts (alert-success, alert-danger) for flash messages
- Implement dismissible alerts with close button (alert-dismissible)
- Display flash messages from RedirectAttributes after POST operations
